     "script": "Welcome to Prophecy and Persia: Cyrus, Islam and the Imam Mahdi. In front of you stands the towering stone gateway of Persepolis, its colossal winged bull-men keeping watch as they have for millennia. This exhibition, presented by the Department for Outreach and Public Relations of the Ahmadiyya Muslim Community UK, follows a single remarkable thread through history, in three parts. First, we meet Cyrus the Great, the Persian emperor whom the Holy Quran may call Dhul-Qarnain. Then we witness the Rise of Islam and Persia's place within it. Finally, we come to the Promised Messiah, the awaited reformer of Persian origin, the Imam Mahdi. The artefacts you will encounter along the way are courtesy of Razwan Baig and the Barlas Foundation. This audio guide will accompany you at every board, and is available in several languages. Take your time, and let the journey begin."
